List the new-gtlds filter in the usage output (Paul Wouters)

When iterating the hash table to free it, must save "next" pointer before
freeing the current entry.

Use ?= instead of = in Makefile for variables that could be set externally
(Paul Wouters).
Safer comparison of signed integer array (thanks Paul Wouters)
Forgot to include new_gtlds.h in the release tarball
Fix arg signedness problem reported by Paul Wouters
document new-gtlds changes
document new-gtlds filter

Adding the "new-gtlds" filter.  This will count messages for which
the TLD ends with one of the newly-approved generic TLDs referenced
here: https://newgtlds.icann.org/newgtlds.csv

Organizations may be particularly interested to use this filter to
find potential name collisions before they happen.
Updating list of known TLDs
update

Update table of DNS type strings so fewer query types are printed
as #NNN?.

use of strcasestr() in looking for "port" in the bpf_program_str
option meant that dnstop doesn't compile on Solaris.  The
case-insensitive check seems superfluous anyway since libcpap won't
recognized mixed-case terms like "Port".  So we can just use strstr()
and keep Soarlis users happy.
